article.headline: East Tenn. St. 79, Elon University 67
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Travis Strong and Tim Smith combined for 51 points as ETSU beat Elon 79-67 Saturday. The Buccaneers (6-9, 2-3 Southern Conference) jumped to an 11-4 lead in the first 3 and a half minutes and led the entire game. Elon (2-15, 0-4) pulled to within 10 with 1:28 left in the half, but ETSU went on a 6-0 run including 4 points by Strong and led 40-24 at the half. Elon opened the second half with a 13-3 run to cut ETSU's lead to 6 with 15 minutes left. Chris Chalko accounted for 8 of the 13 points. But ETSU answered with a 9-0 run to build its lead to 15, with Smith getting 5 points. Elon never got closer than 8 the rest of the game. Scottie Rice led Elon in scoring with 21 points, while Brian Waters added 16 and Chalko 15. The Buccaneers were led by Strong's 26 points and Smith's 25. ETSU shot 61 percent from the field compared with Elon's 46 percent.
